title: Ceiling Border, 1875–1906
creditline: Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds
description:
Wallpaper roll.
Large-scale floral branch set within a circular medallion. Stylized foliate motifs on two sides. Printed in shades of mauve, blue, tan and brown on metallic gold, textile-embossed ground.
